WEBVTT

00:04.226 --> 00:05.087
Welcome to Life Church.

00:05.487 --> 00:09.071
We're here to help you become who God created you to be, and we'd love to hear from you.

00:09.632 --> 00:15.578
Take a quick survey at life.church slash podcast connect to let us know how we can support you on your faith journey.

00:15.978 --> 00:17.300
And now let's go to the message.

00:26.910 --> 00:30.674
So it was sometime in 2017,

00:30.914 --> 00:36.160
or so that I was in my normal place, sitting by my best friend.

00:36.681 --> 00:40.265
And actually I wasn't sitting, I was standing because it was in worship.

00:40.866 --> 00:43.029
And I had had a really normal week.

00:43.049 --> 00:50.478
I had been in God's Word, full of faith, praying, and worshiping about to go and share God's Word.

00:51.079 --> 00:54.182
And it was the weirdest thing, and I promise it was the weirdest thing.

00:54.483 --> 00:57.266
It hadn't happened before and it hadn't happened since.

00:58.274 --> 01:09.187
But when I was about to preach, I just had this random thought, like doubts flooded my mind, and I just thought, like, what if all this stuff isn't real?

01:10.108 --> 01:10.569
And crazy.

01:11.410 --> 01:12.011
No reason.

01:12.912 --> 01:15.956
Just like this, like this paralyzing fear.

01:16.016 --> 01:19.940
Like, what if all this stuff that I've built my whole life on is a lie?

01:20.922 --> 01:26.468
And I had, I don't, you know, I have compassion for people with anxiety.

01:26.508 --> 01:27.890
I don't have anxiety.

01:28.002 --> 01:31.006
I felt anxious and I just thought, I can't preach.

01:31.106 --> 01:34.590
I looked at the exit and I thought, I just need to escape.

01:36.773 --> 01:37.314
I don't know where.

01:38.835 --> 01:39.917
I was just flooded with doubts.

01:41.719 --> 01:47.426
So maybe some of you can relate.

01:49.048 --> 01:56.978
Perhaps for you it wasn't just a moment of doubt, but unfortunately for some people it might be like a season of doubt.

01:57.762 --> 02:02.768
And for some of you, it might not have been like in a shirt like it was for me.

02:03.869 --> 02:10.938
But maybe you were in a hospital room and got a diagnosis that you didn't want to hear.

02:10.998 --> 02:16.024
Or maybe you were at a funeral and you were fighting back the tears.

02:16.965 --> 02:22.732
And you were wondering, God, why didn't you do what I begged you in prayer to do?

02:22.772 --> 02:24.754
You're flooded with doubts.

02:25.282 --> 02:33.192
Maybe it was your alone in your bedroom at 2 a.m. in the morning, crying out to God, wondering if he's even there.

02:33.252 --> 02:42.945
And you ask questions, like, if God is good, and I really believe he is, but if he is, why do I hurt so much?

02:44.667 --> 02:53.138
Or you wonder, if God is so powerful and loves me, why doesn't he fix what's broken in my life?

02:54.434 --> 02:56.336
And your mind races.

02:57.077 --> 03:03.085
If God can do anything, why doesn't he do what his word says he can do?

03:05.107 --> 03:08.692
Why do I feel like he's not there when I need him most?

03:10.154 --> 03:15.601
If you've never had questions like that, you might just take a moment to praise God, right, where you are.

03:16.161 --> 03:23.090
Because for most of us, it's not a matter of if we have a faith question or two,

03:23.202 --> 03:24.624
But it's more like when we do.

03:24.644 --> 03:35.299
And it kind of raises the question like what do you do when one moment you're full of faith and then maybe something else happens and all of a sudden you have faith questions.

03:35.359 --> 03:39.685
What do you do whenever your doubts become louder than your faith?

03:40.726 --> 03:44.972
And so we're talking about a new book that we just released.

03:44.992 --> 03:47.556
It's called The Benefit of Doubts.

03:48.117 --> 03:52.082
And we're talking about how asking real questions can actually help you grow

03:52.194 --> 04:03.967
and your faith, and what I wanna do is just like very sincerely and very pastorally, even though this may be something different than you've ever heard from a pastor before, I wanna give you permission to doubt.

04:05.369 --> 04:16.701
But not just to doubt for the sake of doubt, but to ask sincere spiritual questions in a way that can actually draw you closer to God.

04:17.702 --> 04:21.266
And I wanna show you how to do it from God's word

04:21.506 --> 04:31.877
how to specifically wrestle with some of the real life pain issues that most of us go through without losing your faith in God.

04:32.618 --> 04:40.286
Because as we said in previous weeks, kind of a key idea behind the message of the book is that doubt isn't the enemy of faith.

04:41.487 --> 04:47.794
But doubt is often a pathway to a deeper and more meaningful faith.

04:48.514 --> 04:53.019
If you do find yourself doubting, that doesn't make you a bad Christian.

04:53.079 --> 04:55.582
It makes you a human being.

04:55.602 --> 04:59.266
And it doesn't mean that you're actually running from God.

04:59.286 --> 05:03.110
It may mean that you're really sincerely seeking God.

05:04.071 --> 05:08.456
Doubt is often a pathway to a deeper and more meaningful faith.

05:09.177 --> 05:09.838
So let's pray.

05:09.858 --> 05:13.842
Father, I thank you for every person that you've brought to hear this message.

05:14.530 --> 05:17.933
I pray, God, that your Holy Spirit would do a work in us.

05:18.013 --> 05:26.862
And God, especially for those who may be hurting, who may be struggling in their faith, who may not even know what they believe about you.

05:26.942 --> 05:34.649
Would your Holy Spirit, God, draw us close to you and teach us to trust you, God.

05:34.689 --> 05:42.696
Even when we have questions, God, to trust you, especially when we have questions, because you are always good and you are always with us.

05:43.437 --> 05:44.498
Draw us close.

05:44.610 --> 05:50.418
We pray in the name of Jesus and all God's people said, amen.

05:50.438 --> 05:51.620
Are you ready for the word today?

05:51.640 --> 05:52.601
If you're ready, Sam, ready.

05:53.863 --> 05:56.687
Online type in the comment section, I'm ready for the word.

05:56.727 --> 05:57.648
I'm ready for the word.

05:57.669 --> 06:08.624
What we're gonna do today is I'm gonna show you just a ridiculously powerful example from an Old Testament prophet named Habakkuk.

06:09.766 --> 06:12.850
When you say Habakkuk, you almost have to act like you're clearing your throat.

06:13.346 --> 06:15.529
Like what do you have to do?

06:15.549 --> 06:16.551
And so go ahead and try that.

06:18.113 --> 06:20.537
Now wipe the spit off the back of your head.

06:20.557 --> 06:22.761
He went there right now.

06:24.123 --> 06:31.715
He is the prophet that didn't understand what was going on and still tried to trust God even though he didn't understand.

06:32.075 --> 06:36.402
And if you don't know anything about Habakkuk, he's one of the 12 minor prophets.

